   Instructions for setup of lithuanian language into your PGP:
    (steps A-L for all platforms, steps M-R for DOS platform)

A. !!! Save old LANGUAGE.TXT, CONFIG.TXT and PUBLIC.PGP files !!!

B. Create subdirectory \LT from main PGP subdirectory.

C. Copy received PGP23LTK.ZIP archive file into this \LT subdirectory
   and use appropriate (PKUNZIP or UNZIP) utility to extract few files:
   PKUNZIP PGP23LTK [Enter] or
   UNZIP   PGP23LTK [Enter]

D. After extraction You'll get 7 files:

   PGP23LTK.ME  - This 'read me' file
   PGP23LTK.DIZ - 'File-ID' file (package description)
   PGP23LT1.ZIP - Main Lithuanian Language Kit for PGP 2.3a
   PGP23LT1.SIG - PGP signature file for PGP23LT1.ZIP file
   PGP23LT2.ZIP - DOS Video/Keyboard Drivers for this Kit
   PGP23LT2.SIG - PGP signature file for PGP23LT2.ZIP file
   PGP23LTK.PGP - PGP Public KeyFile for Lithuanian Language Kit.

E. Copy received PGP23LTK.PGP KeyFile to PUBRING.PGP (not recommended) or
   include received PGP public keys from PGP23LTK.PGP KeyFile into main
   PUBRING.PGP keyring typing:
   PGP PGP23LTK.PGP [Enter]

F. Check if received files are not tampered or corrupted:
   PGP PGP23LT1.SIG PGP23LT1.ZIP [Enter]
   PGP PGP23LT2.SIG PGP23LT2.ZIP [Enter]

G. If PGP23LT1.ZIP file was not corrupted extract Main Lithuanian
   Language Kit files typing:
   PKUNZIP PGP23LT1 [Enter] or
   UNZIP   PGP23LT1 [Enter]

H. After extraction You'll get 5 files
   (PGP23LTK.ME and PGP23LTK.PGP are the same as in step 'C'):

   LANGUAGE.LT  - English/lithuanian language file, includes language files:
                  en  - original english language
                  lt  - 7-bit lithuanian language with Latin only characters
                  lt3 - 8-bit lithuanian language characters
   LT.HLP       - PGP 2.3a lithuanian language help file
                  (7-bit latin characters)
   LT3.HLP      - PGP 2.3a lithuanian language help file
                  (8-bit lithuanian characters)
   PGP23LTK.ME  - The same 'read me' file as in step 'C'.
   PGP23LTK.PGP - PGP Public KeyFile for Lithuanian Language Kit
                  (the same as in step 'C').

I. Copy LT.HLP, LT3.HLP and LANGUAGE.LT files to main PGP subdirectory.

J. Merge LANGUAGE.LT file into LANGUAGE.TXT file if You have PGPTOOL
   package or rename LANGUAGE.LT to LANGUAGE.TXT if not.

K. Modify CONFIG.TXT file in PGP subdirectory as follows:

   Language=lt3   - for lithuanian 8-bit character set
                    (if you work in DOS and will use drivers supplied)
   Language=lt    - for lithuanian 7-bit character set
   Charset=latin1

L. Check the contents of received PGP23LTK.PGP KeyFile file, typing:
   PGP -kc PGP23LTK.PGP [Enter]

