      *** If You work in DOS there are some Video/Keyboard drivers ***
      *** supplied with this Lithuanian Language Kit for PGP 2.3a. ***

M. If PGP23LT2.ZIP file was not corrupted extract Video/Keyboard drivers
   for Lithuanian Language Kit typing:
   PKUNZIP PGP23LT2 [Enter] or
   UNZIP   PGP23LT2 [Enter]

N. After extraction You'll get 2 files:

   LT.CPI       - DOS EGA video driver, includes fonts for:
                  latin / lithuanian / cyrillic / graphics characters
   LT.COM       - Keyboard driver (so called Baltic-Amadeus keyboard layout)

O. A video driver must be configured in AUTOEXEC.BAT file if You choosed
   'lt3' language and want to see lithuanian characters on the screen:

   NLSFUNC.EXE
   MODE CON CODEPAGE PREPARE = ((850) LT.CPI)
   CHCP 850

P. A keyboard driver must be configured in AUTOEXEC.BAT file if You
   want to use keyboard driver supplied:

   LT.COM

Q. The line which follows must be entered in CONFIG.SYS:

   DEVICE=DISPLAY.SYS CON:=(EGA,437,1)

R. Reboot the system an run PGP.


